info.name: Agency Parameters API
info.description:
# Introduction ### API for Agency Parameters(s) information belonging to specific banks which is available in PBD system. ### Exposes endpoints to enable clients to _add, remove & modify_ bank agency parameters. These endpoints, however, are access restricted and client must have the neccessary privileges to utilize them. ### _Bank code_ wherever applicable for agency parameters(s) being interacted with using the below endpoints, is grabbed from the _request header_ unless specifically requested in the input parameters. # API summary with common use cases ## 1. _List bank agency parameters available in PBD System_. Clients can get a list of all the available agency parameters present with PBD for the bank for which the request is being made. Response will contain all agency parameters with their basic information details.
This endpoint contains a `view` input to specify how much details is expected in the response. More info can is given in the input specification. --- ## 2. _Create a bank Agency Parameters._ This operation is used to create agency parameters. Clients can create and add a new bank agency parameters to their list of existing agency parameters.
Endpoint responds back with the new bank agency parameters upon successful creation with its ETag value in the response header. This endpoint is access restricted and requires the user to have the proper privileges to perform this operation. --- ## 3. _Update a bank agency parameters_ Clients can update an existing bank agency parameters record to change/edit information. Complete bank agency parameters record is expected along the with the modified fields. If not provided it may result in failure or setting of default/NULL values in missing fields.
Response contains the updated bank agency parameters record with its ETag value in response header.
This too is an access restricted endpoint and requires the user to have the proper privileges to perform the operation. --- ## 4. _Read information for a single bank agency parameter_ Information for a specific bank agency parameters can be accessed via this endpoint. Response contains the complete data just for the requested agency parameters along with the ETag value in the response header.
--- ## 5. _Close/Delete a bank agency parameters_ This operation is used to close/delete agency parameters by pk and version.
This endpoint can close/delete an agency parameters. Successful response will give complete information of agency parameters.
--- # Error response information ``` { "system": "PBD", "code": "3700", "message": "Input error.", "params": null, "applicationSpecific": { "severity": "INPUT_ERROR", "logref": "b85946f2-3044-11e9-b210-d663bd873d93", "message": "Input error.", "validationErrors": [ { errorCode: 3700 errorMessage: page-size maximum value should not exceed 500. } ], "cause": "string" "strackTrace": "string" } } ```
Field Description
system The system short name. Always PBD.
code Error code, identifies uniquely an error type.
message Error message in English describing the error/information situation
params Optional dynamic parameters - can be used to construct an error message in the client.
severity Describes the system level severity of the exception.
logref A log reference associated with the failed request that can be used by support personnel to filter server logs for diagnostic purpose. The caller of the api should save this log reference with its own incident data so it can be part of an incident report.
message Contains addition information about the response in case of an exception.
validationErrors Optional, array of additional details for validation exceptions with errorCode and errorMessage objects.
cause This is development mode property and won't be visible on live. Contains root cause for the exception.
stackTrace This is development mode property and won't be visible on live. Contains the stack trace of the exception.
